Would you like to be a Parish Councillor?

Parish Elections for Hixon Parish Council are to be held on 2nd May 2019. The Nomination Packs will be available from Monday 4 March from the Elections Office, Civic Centre, Riverside, Stafford ST16 3AQ. For further information on how to become a councillor, please read on and click on the links:
Read More...

Hixon Parish Council is seeking to create a new user-friendly website to assist the Council to better interact with the local community, statutory bodies and interested parties around the world. To this end, Hixon Parish Council invites EXPRESSIONS OF INTEREST from suitably experienced website designers and maintenance providers. If that sound like you, please email clerk@hixon.gov.uk
Read More...

The presentation of the Best Garden Awards took place on the evening of 24th October in the Bank House. Read on for full results....
Read More...

If you have any ideas for new classes, clubs, events etc. that you would like to have in Hixon, please contact Karen Appleton on 01889 270151. Please follow link for updated timetable at the Memorial Hall (November 2017). Contact Karen Appleton on 01889 270151 to book the hall.

Read More...

Read More...

There is a community Facebook page available to residents of the parishes of Hixon and Stowe by Chartley. It is the Hixon Parish Stafford Community Forum, if you want to get to it please click this link

It is a closed group so you will have to request to join from from the page itself.
Read More...

Hixon Parish Council would like to ask residents to take back inside any items that have been left out for the scrap collectors but not collected, after 2-3 days.
Read More...

Home 

The Council’s work is administered by a part-time paid clerk, Mrs Catherine Gill , see contacts page. The Council represents the interests of the people of Hixon and comments on all matters that impact on the community. Please use the tabs above to see further information and current news on various matters.
